In vitro fluorescence images also showed the tumor-specific homing of macrophages. Macrophages migrated to the tumor within 1 h and remained there for up to 6 h (Fig. 5
 and Table 1
). During the first hour, GQD and GQD-loaded macrophages spread to all organs (the kidney, liver, lung, spleen, and tumor); however, GQD-loaded macrophages continued to accumulate in the tumor tissue for up to 6 h. GQD-loaded macrophages showed higher ex vivo fluorescence than GQDs alone (Fig. 5a). The fluorescence of GQD-loaded macrophages in the tumor gradually decreased until 6–48 h (Fig. 5b).

